verbose_text: It has been suggested that binding of TWEAK to Fn14 extracellular domain leads to receptor trimerization, association of TRAF2 / cIAP1 (cellular inhibitor of apoptosis protein 1) complex to cytoplasmic domain, and subsequent activation of various signaling proteins including TRAF6, transforming growth factor-beta activated kinase1 (TAK1), I kappa B kinase (IKK), and MAPKs leading to altered expression of several genes involved in various cellular responses [XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR - XREF_BIBR].
